column5: My buddy ( non fisherman ) has purchased a property on Davis Lake near Kinmount. I have never heard of it so I told my buddy I would do a little research. So here I am. Does anyone know anything about this lake ? P.M. if you prefer
Smaller lake, lots of cottages, it used to have a natural lake trout population, pretty sure they're gone now, ok bass fishing
Driven along Davis Lake Rd. many times, very pretty looking little lake.
a TON of rockbass in there as recall from about 6+ years ago.
Everybody is related?  "If your family tree does not fork... you might be a redneck." - Jeff Foxworthy
still quite few lake trout..fish it cpl times a yr with steel line..  trouble is catching the 1's you can keep...slot sizes..smallies are plentiful..
because they couldn't put Cousin*%#$ on a map!!
